short_description:
By means an indexes matrix with 'n' rows, this class creates an abstract nested loop with 'n' levels and 'n' indexes or counter variables. 

Indexes matrix has Nx3 dimension and this format: 
{
    { start1, end1, step1 },
    { start2, end2, step2 },
     ...
    { startN, endN, stepN }
 } 

'start', 'end' and 'step' are double. 'end' is inclusive and if is lower than 'start', loop will have 0 iterations. The loop is designed to be increased (negative steps result in infinite loops). 

Example:
{
    { 0, 9, 1 },
    { 1, 2, 1 },
    { -10, 10, 4 }
}
This matrix represents the following nested loops;

for ( i = 0; i <= 9; i++ )
    for ( j = 1; j <= 2; j++ )
        for ( k = -10; k <= 10; k += 4 )
            // do something
